Skills

| am passionate about art and technology. | was denied the opportunity to become an artist by my father, with

him quoting the “starving artist” phenomenon when | was 14 years old. Ever since then, | am determined to /
solve this issue so that no future generation would be denied their artistic dream purely because of monetary Experience
problems. With the advancement of computer vision, extended reality, and machine learning, alongside time
and experience, | firmly believe that such a solution to the “starving artist” lies in the intersection of art and

technology.

Research

Innovation must happen for the problem of “starving artists” to disappear. There is a reason why such a
phenomenon exists for most artists, and without some form of breakthrough, such bleak reality will continue
to exist. | want to devote myself to the research of such innovation, be it computer vision, extended reality, or
artificial intelligence. With hard work and resilience, | will contribute to such innovation.

Startup

During my leave from Berkeley, | tried my hands at founding my own startup. | interviewed about 200 artists,
asking them what's their biggest issue and how can | help. The most common ones | get are the following:
1.Piracy Issue 2.Connection with other artists 3.Monetary Issue | plan to use my knowledge from research to
continue to explore and help to solve these problems and more.

My Skills and Values

Python, C++, Swift, Web Development, iOS development, knowledge of startup, knowledge of art
